author: COMSOL
description: This example is a benchmark problem for simulating phase change in porous media. It studies the melting process of an ice inclusion within porous media and therefore demonstrates how to couple Darcy's Law with the Heat Transfer in Porous Media interface including phase change. It is one of the test cases from the INTERFROST project - an intercomparison project for coupled thermo-hydraulic systems with respect to climate change in permafrost regions.
